Brazilian Stock Movers: Autometal, Rossi, MMX, Petrobras

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-09-02T20:41:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/brazilian-stock-movers-b2w-mmx-mineracao-petrobras-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 2.7 percent to 56,531.62.  Autometal SA (AUTM3 BS) rose 1.5 percent to 13.39 reais.
The Brazilian unit of Spanish auto-parts maker  Cie Automotive SA (CIE) 
was rated “buy” in new coverage at Banco BTG Pactual SA.  Rossi Residencial SA (RSID3 BS) declined 6.9 percent to
12.20 reais. The homebuilder led declines by companies that
depend on credit growth as traders reduced bets for lower
borrowing costs in  Brazil .  MMX Mineracao & Metalicos SA (MMXM3 BS) dropped 5.1 percent
to 8.03 reais. The iron-ore producer controlled by Brazilian
billionaire Eike Batista was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at
Bank of America Corp.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS) declined 3.2 percent to
20.37 reais. Brazil’s government is studying increasing a
special participation tax on oil production that may raise
revenue by 3 billion reais ($1.8 billion), Valor Economico
newspaper reported today, without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  